stm32f4xx.h
Go to the documentation of this file.
1 /**
2  ******************************************************************************
3  * @file stm32f4xx.h
4  * @author MCD Application Team
5  * @version V1.0.0
6  * @date 30-September-2011
7  * @brief CMSIS Cortex-M4 Device Peripheral Access Layer Header File.
8  * This file contains all the peripheral register's definitions, bits
9  * definitions and memory mapping for STM32F4xx devices.
10  *
11  * The file is the unique include file that the application programmer
12  * is using in the C source code, usually in main.c. This file contains:
13  * - Configuration section that allows to select:
14  * - The device used in the target application
15  * - To use or not the peripheral’s drivers in application code(i.e.
16  * code will be based on direct access to peripheral’s registers
17  * rather than drivers API), this option is controlled by
18  * "#define USE_STDPERIPH_DRIVER"
19  * - To change few application-specific parameters such as the HSE
20  * crystal frequency
21  * - Data structures and the address mapping for all peripherals
22  * - Peripheral's registers declarations and bits definition
23  * - Macros to access peripheral’s registers hardware
24  *
25  ******************************************************************************
26  * @attention
27  *
28  * THE PRESENT FIRMWARE WHICH IS FOR GUIDANCE ONLY AIMS AT PROVIDING CUSTOMERS
29  * WITH CODING INFORMATION REGARDING THEIR PRODUCTS IN ORDER FOR THEM TO SAVE
30  * TIME. AS A RESULT, STMICROELECTRONICS SHALL NOT BE HELD LIABLE FOR ANY
31  * DIRECT, INDIRECT OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES WITH RESPECT TO ANY CLAIMS ARISING
32  * FROM THE CONTENT OF SUCH FIRMWARE AND/OR THE USE MADE BY CUSTOMERS OF THE
33  * CODING INFORMATION CONTAINED HEREIN IN CONNECTION WITH THEIR PRODUCTS.
34  *
35  * <h2><center>&copy; COPYRIGHT 2011 STMicroelectronics</center></h2>
36  ******************************************************************************
37  */

109 /**
110  * @brief STM32F4XX Standard Peripherals Library version number V1.0.0
111  */
112 #define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_MAIN (0x01) /*!< [31:24] main version */
113 #define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB1 (0x00) /*!< [23:16] sub1 version */
114 #define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB2 (0x00) /*!< [15:8] sub2 version */
115 #define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_RC (0x00) /*!< [7:0] release candidate */
116 #define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION ((__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_MAIN << 24)
117  |(__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB1 << 16)
118  |(__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB2 << 8)
119  |(__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_RC))

143 /**
144  * @brief STM32F4XX Interrupt Number Definition, according to the selected device
145  * in @ref Library_configuration_section
146  */
147 typedef enum IRQn
148 {
149 /****** Cortex-M4 Processor Exceptions Numbers ****************************************************************/
150  NonMaskableInt_IRQn = -14, /*!< 2 Non Maskable Interrupt */
151  MemoryManagement_IRQn = -12, /*!< 4 Cortex-M4 Memory Management Interrupt */
152  BusFault_IRQn = -11, /*!< 5 Cortex-M4 Bus Fault Interrupt */
153  UsageFault_IRQn = -10, /*!< 6 Cortex-M4 Usage Fault Interrupt */
154  SVCall_IRQn = -5, /*!< 11 Cortex-M4 SV Call Interrupt */
155  DebugMonitor_IRQn = -4, /*!< 12 Cortex-M4 Debug Monitor Interrupt */
156  PendSV_IRQn = -2, /*!< 14 Cortex-M4 Pend SV Interrupt */
157  SysTick_IRQn = -1, /*!< 15 Cortex-M4 System Tick Interrupt */
158 /****** STM32 specific Interrupt Numbers **********************************************************************/
159  WWDG_IRQn = 0, /*!< Window WatchDog Interrupt */
160  PVD_IRQn = 1, /*!< PVD through EXTI Line detection Interrupt */
161  TAMP_STAMP_IRQn = 2, /*!< Tamper and TimeStamp interrupts through the EXTI line */
162  RTC_WKUP_IRQn = 3, /*!< RTC Wakeup interrupt through the EXTI line */
163  FLASH_IRQn = 4, /*!< FLASH global Interrupt */
164  RCC_IRQn = 5, /*!< RCC global Interrupt */
165  EXTI0_IRQn = 6, /*!< EXTI Line0 Interrupt */
166  EXTI1_IRQn = 7, /*!< EXTI Line1 Interrupt */
167  EXTI2_IRQn = 8, /*!< EXTI Line2 Interrupt */
168  EXTI3_IRQn = 9, /*!< EXTI Line3 Interrupt */
169  EXTI4_IRQn = 10, /*!< EXTI Line4 Interrupt */
170  DMA1_Stream0_IRQn = 11, /*!< DMA1 Stream 0 global Interrupt */
171  DMA1_Stream1_IRQn = 12, /*!< DMA1 Stream 1 global Interrupt */
172  DMA1_Stream2_IRQn = 13, /*!< DMA1 Stream 2 global Interrupt */
173  DMA1_Stream3_IRQn = 14, /*!< DMA1 Stream 3 global Interrupt */
174  DMA1_Stream4_IRQn = 15, /*!< DMA1 Stream 4 global Interrupt */
175  DMA1_Stream5_IRQn = 16, /*!< DMA1 Stream 5 global Interrupt */
176  DMA1_Stream6_IRQn = 17, /*!< DMA1 Stream 6 global Interrupt */
177  ADC_IRQn = 18, /*!< ADC1, ADC2 and ADC3 global Interrupts */
178  CAN1_TX_IRQn = 19, /*!< CAN1 TX Interrupt */
179  CAN1_RX0_IRQn = 20, /*!< CAN1 RX0 Interrupt */
180  CAN1_RX1_IRQn = 21, /*!< CAN1 RX1 Interrupt */
181  CAN1_SCE_IRQn = 22, /*!< CAN1 SCE Interrupt */
182  EXTI9_5_IRQn = 23, /*!< External Line[9:5] Interrupts */
183  TIM1_BRK_TIM9_IRQn = 24, /*!< TIM1 Break interrupt and TIM9 global interrupt */
184  TIM1_UP_TIM10_IRQn = 25, /*!< TIM1 Update Interrupt and TIM10 global interrupt */
185  TIM1_TRG_COM_TIM11_IRQn = 26, /*!< TIM1 Trigger and Commutation Interrupt and TIM11 global interrupt */
186  TIM1_CC_IRQn = 27, /*!< TIM1 Capture Compare Interrupt */
187  TIM2_IRQn = 28, /*!< TIM2 global Interrupt */
188  TIM3_IRQn = 29, /*!< TIM3 global Interrupt */
189  TIM4_IRQn = 30, /*!< TIM4 global Interrupt */
190  I2C1_EV_IRQn = 31, /*!< I2C1 Event Interrupt */
191  I2C1_ER_IRQn = 32, /*!< I2C1 Error Interrupt */
192  I2C2_EV_IRQn = 33, /*!< I2C2 Event Interrupt */
193  I2C2_ER_IRQn = 34, /*!< I2C2 Error Interrupt */
194  SPI1_IRQn = 35, /*!< SPI1 global Interrupt */
195  SPI2_IRQn = 36, /*!< SPI2 global Interrupt */
196  USART1_IRQn = 37, /*!< USART1 global Interrupt */
197  USART2_IRQn = 38, /*!< USART2 global Interrupt */
198  USART3_IRQn = 39, /*!< USART3 global Interrupt */
199  EXTI15_10_IRQn = 40, /*!< External Line[15:10] Interrupts */
200  RTC_Alarm_IRQn = 41, /*!< RTC Alarm (A and B) through EXTI Line Interrupt */
201  OTG_FS_WKUP_IRQn = 42, /*!< USB OTG FS Wakeup through EXTI line interrupt */
202  TIM8_BRK_TIM12_IRQn = 43, /*!< TIM8 Break Interrupt and TIM12 global interrupt */
203  TIM8_UP_TIM13_IRQn = 44, /*!< TIM8 Update Interrupt and TIM13 global interrupt */
204  TIM8_TRG_COM_TIM14_IRQn = 45, /*!< TIM8 Trigger and Commutation Interrupt and TIM14 global interrupt */
205  TIM8_CC_IRQn = 46, /*!< TIM8 Capture Compare Interrupt */
206  DMA1_Stream7_IRQn = 47, /*!< DMA1 Stream7 Interrupt */
207  FSMC_IRQn = 48, /*!< FSMC global Interrupt */
208  SDIO_IRQn = 49, /*!< SDIO global Interrupt */
209  TIM5_IRQn = 50, /*!< TIM5 global Interrupt */
210  SPI3_IRQn = 51, /*!< SPI3 global Interrupt */
211  UART4_IRQn = 52, /*!< UART4 global Interrupt */
212  UART5_IRQn = 53, /*!< UART5 global Interrupt */
213  TIM6_DAC_IRQn = 54, /*!< TIM6 global and DAC1&2 underrun error interrupts */
214  TIM7_IRQn = 55, /*!< TIM7 global interrupt */
215  DMA2_Stream0_IRQn = 56, /*!< DMA2 Stream 0 global Interrupt */
216  DMA2_Stream1_IRQn = 57, /*!< DMA2 Stream 1 global Interrupt */
217  DMA2_Stream2_IRQn = 58, /*!< DMA2 Stream 2 global Interrupt */
218  DMA2_Stream3_IRQn = 59, /*!< DMA2 Stream 3 global Interrupt */
219  DMA2_Stream4_IRQn = 60, /*!< DMA2 Stream 4 global Interrupt */
220  ETH_IRQn = 61, /*!< Ethernet global Interrupt */
221  ETH_WKUP_IRQn = 62, /*!< Ethernet Wakeup through EXTI line Interrupt */
222  CAN2_TX_IRQn = 63, /*!< CAN2 TX Interrupt */
223  CAN2_RX0_IRQn = 64, /*!< CAN2 RX0 Interrupt */
224  CAN2_RX1_IRQn = 65, /*!< CAN2 RX1 Interrupt */
225  CAN2_SCE_IRQn = 66, /*!< CAN2 SCE Interrupt */
226  OTG_FS_IRQn = 67, /*!< USB OTG FS global Interrupt */
227  DMA2_Stream5_IRQn = 68, /*!< DMA2 Stream 5 global interrupt */
228  DMA2_Stream6_IRQn = 69, /*!< DMA2 Stream 6 global interrupt */
229  DMA2_Stream7_IRQn = 70, /*!< DMA2 Stream 7 global interrupt */
230  USART6_IRQn = 71, /*!< USART6 global interrupt */
231  I2C3_EV_IRQn = 72, /*!< I2C3 event interrupt */
232  I2C3_ER_IRQn = 73, /*!< I2C3 error interrupt */
233  OTG_HS_EP1_OUT_IRQn = 74, /*!< USB OTG HS End Point 1 Out global interrupt */
234  OTG_HS_EP1_IN_IRQn = 75, /*!< USB OTG HS End Point 1 In global interrupt */
235  OTG_HS_WKUP_IRQn = 76, /*!< USB OTG HS Wakeup through EXTI interrupt */
236  OTG_HS_IRQn = 77, /*!< USB OTG HS global interrupt */
237  DCMI_IRQn = 78, /*!< DCMI global interrupt */
238  CRYP_IRQn = 79, /*!< CRYP crypto global interrupt */
239  HASH_RNG_IRQn = 80, /*!< Hash and Rng global interrupt */
240  FPU_IRQn = 81 /*!< FPU global interrupt */
241 } IRQn_Type;

302 /**
303  * @brief Analog to Digital Converter
304  */
305 
306 typedef struct
307 {
308  __IO uint32_t SR; /*!< ADC status register, Address offset: 0x00 */
309  __IO uint32_t CR1; /*!< ADC control register 1, Address offset: 0x04 */
310  __IO uint32_t CR2; /*!< ADC control register 2, Address offset: 0x08 */
311  __IO uint32_t SMPR1; /*!< ADC sample time register 1, Address offset: 0x0C */
312  __IO uint32_t SMPR2; /*!< ADC sample time register 2, Address offset: 0x10 */
313  __IO uint32_t JOFR1; /*!< ADC injected channel data offset register 1, Address offset: 0x14 */
314  __IO uint32_t JOFR2; /*!< ADC injected channel data offset register 2, Address offset: 0x18 */
315  __IO uint32_t JOFR3; /*!< ADC injected channel data offset register 3, Address offset: 0x1C */
316  __IO uint32_t JOFR4; /*!< ADC injected channel data offset register 4, Address offset: 0x20 */
317  __IO uint32_t HTR; /*!< ADC watchdog higher threshold register, Address offset: 0x24 */
318  __IO uint32_t LTR; /*!< ADC watchdog lower threshold register, Address offset: 0x28 */
319  __IO uint32_t SQR1; /*!< ADC regular sequence register 1, Address offset: 0x2C */
320  __IO uint32_t SQR2; /*!< ADC regular sequence register 2, Address offset: 0x30 */
321  __IO uint32_t SQR3; /*!< ADC regular sequence register 3, Address offset: 0x34 */
322  __IO uint32_t JSQR; /*!< ADC injected sequence register, Address offset: 0x38*/
323  __IO uint32_t JDR1; /*!< ADC injected data register 1, Address offset: 0x3C */
324  __IO uint32_t JDR2; /*!< ADC injected data register 2, Address offset: 0x40 */
325  __IO uint32_t JDR3; /*!< ADC injected data register 3, Address offset: 0x44 */
326  __IO uint32_t JDR4; /*!< ADC injected data register 4, Address offset: 0x48 */
327  __IO uint32_t DR; /*!< ADC regular data register, Address offset: 0x4C */
328 } ADC_TypeDef;

332  __IO uint32_t CSR; /*!< ADC Common status register, Address offset: ADC1 base address + 0x300 */
333  __IO uint32_t CCR; /*!< ADC common control register, Address offset: ADC1 base address + 0x304 */
334  __IO uint32_t CDR; /*!< ADC common regular data register for dual
335  AND triple modes, Address offset: ADC1 base address + 0x308 */
336 } ADC_Common_TypeDef;

380  __IO uint32_t MSR; /*!< CAN master status register, Address offset: 0x04 */
381  __IO uint32_t TSR; /*!< CAN transmit status register, Address offset: 0x08 */
382  __IO uint32_t RF0R; /*!< CAN receive FIFO 0 register, Address offset: 0x0C */
383  __IO uint32_t RF1R; /*!< CAN receive FIFO 1 register, Address offset: 0x10 */
384  __IO uint32_t IER; /*!< CAN interrupt enable register, Address offset: 0x14 */
385  __IO uint32_t ESR; /*!< CAN error status register, Address offset: 0x18 */
386  __IO uint32_t BTR; /*!< CAN bit timing register, Address offset: 0x1C */
387  uint32_t RESERVED0[88]; /*!< Reserved, 0x020 - 0x17F */
388  CAN_TxMailBox_TypeDef sTxMailBox[3]; /*!< CAN Tx MailBox, Address offset: 0x180 - 0x1AC */
389  CAN_FIFOMailBox_TypeDef sFIFOMailBox[2]; /*!< CAN FIFO MailBox, Address offset: 0x1B0 - 0x1CC */
390  uint32_t RESERVED1[12]; /*!< Reserved, 0x1D0 - 0x1FF */
391  __IO uint32_t FMR; /*!< CAN filter master register, Address offset: 0x200 */
392  __IO uint32_t FM1R; /*!< CAN filter mode register, Address offset: 0x204 */
393  uint32_t RESERVED2; /*!< Reserved, 0x208 */
394  __IO uint32_t FS1R; /*!< CAN filter scale register, Address offset: 0x20C */
395  uint32_t RESERVED3; /*!< Reserved, 0x210 */
396  __IO uint32_t FFA1R; /*!< CAN filter FIFO assignment register, Address offset: 0x214 */
397  uint32_t RESERVED4; /*!< Reserved, 0x218 */
398  __IO uint32_t FA1R; /*!< CAN filter activation register, Address offset: 0x21C */
399  uint32_t RESERVED5[8]; /*!< Reserved, 0x220-0x23F */
400  CAN_FilterRegister_TypeDef sFilterRegister[28]; /*!< CAN Filter Register, Address offset: 0x240-0x31C */
401 } CAN_TypeDef;

941 typedef struct
942 {

944  __IO uint32_t CFR; /*!< WWDG Configuration register, Address offset: 0x04 */

948 /**
949  * @brief Crypto Processor
950  */
951 
952 typedef struct
953 {
954  __IO uint32_t CR; /*!< CRYP control register, Address offset: 0x00 */
955  __IO uint32_t SR; /*!< CRYP status register, Address offset: 0x04 */
956  __IO uint32_t DR; /*!< CRYP data input register, Address offset: 0x08 */
957  __IO uint32_t DOUT; /*!< CRYP data output register, Address offset: 0x0C */
958  __IO uint32_t DMACR; /*!< CRYP DMA control register, Address offset: 0x10 */
959  __IO uint32_t IMSCR; /*!< CRYP interrupt mask set/clear register, Address offset: 0x14 */
960  __IO uint32_t RISR; /*!< CRYP raw interrupt status register, Address offset: 0x18 */
961  __IO uint32_t MISR; /*!< CRYP masked interrupt status register, Address offset: 0x1C */
962  __IO uint32_t K0LR; /*!< CRYP key left register 0, Address offset: 0x20 */
963  __IO uint32_t K0RR; /*!< CRYP key right register 0, Address offset: 0x24 */
964  __IO uint32_t K1LR; /*!< CRYP key left register 1, Address offset: 0x28 */
965  __IO uint32_t K1RR; /*!< CRYP key right register 1, Address offset: 0x2C */
966  __IO uint32_t K2LR; /*!< CRYP key left register 2, Address offset: 0x30 */
967  __IO uint32_t K2RR; /*!< CRYP key right register 2, Address offset: 0x34 */
968  __IO uint32_t K3LR; /*!< CRYP key left register 3, Address offset: 0x38 */
969  __IO uint32_t K3RR; /*!< CRYP key right register 3, Address offset: 0x3C */
970  __IO uint32_t IV0LR; /*!< CRYP initialization vector left-word register 0, Address offset: 0x40 */
971  __IO uint32_t IV0RR; /*!< CRYP initialization vector right-word register 0, Address offset: 0x44 */
972  __IO uint32_t IV1LR; /*!< CRYP initialization vector left-word register 1, Address offset: 0x48 */
973  __IO uint32_t IV1RR; /*!< CRYP initialization vector right-word register 1, Address offset: 0x4C */
974 } CRYP_TypeDef;

979 
980 typedef struct
981 {
982  __IO uint32_t CR; /*!< HASH control register, Address offset: 0x00 */
983  __IO uint32_t DIN; /*!< HASH data input register, Address offset: 0x04 */
984  __IO uint32_t STR; /*!< HASH start register, Address offset: 0x08 */
985  __IO uint32_t HR[5]; /*!< HASH digest registers, Address offset: 0x0C-0x1C */
986  __IO uint32_t IMR; /*!< HASH interrupt enable register, Address offset: 0x20 */
987  __IO uint32_t SR; /*!< HASH status register, Address offset: 0x24 */
988  uint32_t RESERVED[52]; /*!< Reserved, 0x28-0xF4 */
989  __IO uint32_t CSR[51]; /*!< HASH context swap registers, Address offset: 0x0F8-0x1C0 */
990 } HASH_TypeDef;

1237 /******************************************************************************/

1241 /******************************************************************************/
1242 /* */
1243 /* Analog to Digital Converter */
1244 /* */
1245 /******************************************************************************/
1246 /******************** Bit definition for ADC_SR register ********************/
1247 #define ADC_SR_AWD ((uint8_t)0x01) /*!<Analog watchdog flag */
1248 #define ADC_SR_EOC ((uint8_t)0x02) /*!<End of conversion */
1249 #define ADC_SR_JEOC ((uint8_t)0x04) /*!<Injected channel end of conversion */
1250 #define ADC_SR_JSTRT ((uint8_t)0x08) /*!<Injected channel Start flag */
1251 #define ADC_SR_STRT ((uint8_t)0x10) /*!<Regular channel Start flag */
1252 #define ADC_SR_OVR ((uint8_t)0x20) /*!<Overrun flag */
1253 
1254 /******************* Bit definition for ADC_CR1 register ********************/
1255 #define ADC_CR1_AWDCH ((uint32_t)0x0000001F) /*!<AWDCH[4:0] bits (Analog watchdog channel select bits) */
1256 #define ADC_CR1_AWDCH_0 ((uint32_t)0x00000001) /*!<Bit 0 */
1257 #define ADC_CR1_AWDCH_1 ((uint32_t)0x00000002) /*!<Bit 1 */
1258 #define ADC_CR1_AWDCH_2 ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /*!<Bit 2 */
1259 #define ADC_CR1_AWDCH_3 ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /*!<Bit 3 */
1260 #define ADC_CR1_AWDCH_4 ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /*!<Bit 4 */
1261 #define ADC_CR1_EOCIE ((uint32_t)0x00000020) /*!<Interrupt enable for EOC */
1262 #define ADC_CR1_AWDIE ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /*!<AAnalog Watchdog interrupt enable */
1263 #define ADC_CR1_JEOCIE ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /*!<Interrupt enable for injected channels */
1264 #define ADC_CR1_SCAN ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /*!<Scan mode */
1265 #define ADC_CR1_AWDSGL ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /*!<Enable the watchdog on a single channel in scan mode */
1266 #define ADC_CR1_JAUTO ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /*!<Automatic injected group conversion */
1267 #define ADC_CR1_DISCEN ((uint32_t)0x00000800) /*!<Discontinuous mode on regular channels */
1268 #define ADC_CR1_JDISCEN ((uint32_t)0x00001000) /*!<Discontinuous mode on injected channels */
1269 #define ADC_CR1_DISCNUM ((uint32_t)0x0000E000) /*!<DISCNUM[2:0] bits (Discontinuous mode channel count) */
1270 #define ADC_CR1_DISCNUM_0 ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /*!<Bit 0 */
1271 #define ADC_CR1_DISCNUM_1 ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /*!<Bit 1 */
1272 #define ADC_CR1_DISCNUM_2 ((uint32_t)0x00008000) /*!<Bit 2 */
1273 #define ADC_CR1_JAWDEN ((uint32_t)0x00400000) /*!<Analog watchdog enable on injected channels */
1274 #define ADC_CR1_AWDEN ((uint32_t)0x00800000) /*!<Analog watchdog enable on regular channels */
1275 #define ADC_CR1_RES ((uint32_t)0x03000000) /*!<RES[2:0] bits (Resolution) */
1276 #define ADC_CR1_RES_0 ((uint32_t)0x01000000) /*!<Bit 0 */
1277 #define ADC_CR1_RES_1 ((uint32_t)0x02000000) /*!<Bit 1 */
1278 #define ADC_CR1_OVRIE ((uint32_t)0x04000000) /*!<overrun interrupt enable */
1279 
1280 /******************* Bit definition for ADC_CR2 register ********************/
1281 #define ADC_CR2_ADON ((uint32_t)0x00000001) /*!<A/D Converter ON / OFF */
1282 #define ADC_CR2_CONT ((uint32_t)0x00000002) /*!<Continuous Conversion */
1283 #define ADC_CR2_DMA ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /*!<Direct Memory access mode */
1284 #define ADC_CR2_DDS ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /*!<DMA disable selection (Single ADC) */
1285 #define ADC_CR2_EOCS ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /*!<End of conversion selection */
1286 #define ADC_CR2_ALIGN ((uint32_t)0x00000800) /*!<Data Alignment */
1287 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTSEL ((uint32_t)0x000F0000) /*!<JEXTSEL[3:0] bits (External event select for injected group) */
1288 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTSEL_0 ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /*!<Bit 0 */
1289 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTSEL_1 ((uint32_t)0x00020000) /*!<Bit 1 */
1290 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTSEL_2 ((uint32_t)0x00040000) /*!<Bit 2 */
1291 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTSEL_3 ((uint32_t)0x00080000) /*!<Bit 3 */
1292 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTEN ((uint32_t)0x00300000) /*!<JEXTEN[1:0] bits (External Trigger Conversion mode for injected channelsp) */
1293 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTEN_0 ((uint32_t)0x00100000) /*!<Bit 0 */
1294 #define ADC_CR2_JEXTEN_1 ((uint32_t)0x00200000) /*!<Bit 1 */
1295 #define ADC_CR2_JSWSTART ((uint32_t)0x00400000) /*!<Start Conversion of injected channels */
1296 #define ADC_CR2_EXTSEL ((uint32_t)0x0F000000) /*!<EXTSEL[3:0] bits (External Event Select for regular group) */
1297 #define ADC_CR2_EXTSEL_0 ((uint32_t)0x01000000) /*!<Bit 0 */
1298 #define ADC_CR2_EXTSEL_1 ((uint32_t)0x02000000) /*!<Bit 1 */
1299 #define ADC_CR2_EXTSEL_2 ((uint32_t)0x04000000) /*!<Bit 2 */
1300 #define ADC_CR2_EXTSEL_3 ((uint32_t)0x08000000) /*!<Bit 3 */
1301 #define ADC_CR2_EXTEN ((uint32_t)0x30000000) /*!<EXTEN[1:0] bits (External Trigger Conversion mode for regular channelsp) */

4666 /******************* Bit definition for I2C_SR1 register ********************/
4667 #define I2C_SR1_SB ((uint16_t)0x0001) /*!<Start Bit (Master mode) */
4668 #define I2C_SR1_ADDR ((uint16_t)0x0002) /*!<Address sent (master mode)/matched (slave mode) */
4669 #define I2C_SR1_BTF ((uint16_t)0x0004) /*!<Byte Transfer Finished */
4670 #define I2C_SR1_ADD10 ((uint16_t)0x0008) /*!<10-bit header sent (Master mode) */
4671 #define I2C_SR1_STOPF ((uint16_t)0x0010) /*!<Stop detection (Slave mode) */
4672 #define I2C_SR1_RXNE ((uint16_t)0x0040) /*!<Data Register not Empty (receivers) */
4673 #define I2C_SR1_TXE ((uint16_t)0x0080) /*!<Data Register Empty (transmitters) */

6525 /******************************************************************************/
6526 /* */
6527 /* Ethernet MAC Registers bits definitions */
6528 /* */
6529 /******************************************************************************/
6530 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Control Register register */
6531 #define ETH_MACCR_WD ((uint32_t)0x00800000) /* Watchdog disable */
6532 #define ETH_MACCR_JD ((uint32_t)0x00400000) /* Jabber disable */
6533 #define ETH_MACCR_IFG ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Inter-frame gap */
6534 #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_96Bit ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 96Bit */
6535  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_88Bit ((uint32_t)0x00020000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 88Bit */
6536  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_80Bit ((uint32_t)0x00040000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 80Bit */
6537  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_72Bit ((uint32_t)0x00060000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 72Bit */
6538  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_64Bit ((uint32_t)0x00080000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 64Bit */
6539  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_56Bit ((uint32_t)0x000A0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 56Bit */
6540  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_48Bit ((uint32_t)0x000C0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 48Bit */
6541  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_40Bit ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 40Bit */
6542 #define ETH_MACCR_CSD ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* Carrier sense disable (during transmission) */
6543 #define ETH_MACCR_FES ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* Fast ethernet speed */
6544 #define ETH_MACCR_ROD ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Receive own disable */
6545 #define ETH_MACCR_LM ((uint32_t)0x00001000) /* loopback mode */
6546 #define ETH_MACCR_DM ((uint32_t)0x00000800) /* Duplex mode */
6547 #define ETH_MACCR_IPCO ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* IP Checksum offload */
6548 #define ETH_MACCR_RD ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Retry disable */
6549 #define ETH_MACCR_APCS ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Automatic Pad/CRC stripping */
6550 #define ETH_MACCR_BL ((uint32_t)0x00000060) /* Back-off limit: random integer number (r) of slot time delays before rescheduling
6551  a transmission attempt during retries after a collision: 0 =< r <2^k */
6552  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_10 ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* k = min (n, 10) */
6553  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_8 ((uint32_t)0x00000020) /* k = min (n, 8) */
6554  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_4 ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* k = min (n, 4) */
6555  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_1 ((uint32_t)0x00000060) /* k = min (n, 1) */
6556 #define ETH_MACCR_DC ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /* Defferal check */
6557 #define ETH_MACCR_TE ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* Transmitter enable */
6558 #define ETH_MACCR_RE ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* Receiver enable */
6559 
6560 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Frame Filter Register */
6561 #define ETH_MACFFR_RA ((uint32_t)0x80000000) /* Receive all */
6562 #define ETH_MACFFR_HPF ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* Hash or perfect filter */
6563 #define ETH_MACFFR_SAF ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Source address filter enable */
6564 #define ETH_MACFFR_SAIF ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /* SA inverse filtering */
6565 #define ETH_MACFFR_PCF ((uint32_t)0x000000C0) /* Pass control frames: 3 cases */
